---
import LayoutCore from '../../layouts/LayoutCore.astro';
import GlassCard from '../../components/GlassCard.astro';
---

<LayoutCore
  title="BabyBlocks Core: Coming Soon | BabyBlocks"
  description="BabyBlocks Core is the unified hub of the BabyBlocks ecosystem. One dashboard for your entire daily life: budget, pantry, and everything that comes next. Coming after PantryBaby."
  canonical="/coming-soon/babyblocks-core"
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="core-hero section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="core-inner">
        <div class="core-copy">
          <div class="label-chip">In Planning</div>
          <h1>BabyBlocks<br /><span class="text-gradient">Core</span></h1>
          <p class="core-tagline">The hub that ties it all together.</p>
          <p class="core-desc">
            As the BabyBlocks ecosystem grows, so does the need for a single place to see the whole picture.
            BabyBlocks Core is that place. A unified daily view that brings your budget, pantry,
            and every future app into one calm, coherent dashboard.
          </p>
          <div class="core-timeline">
            <div class="timeline-item timeline-done">
              <span class="tl-dot"></span>
              <div>
                <p class="tl-label">BudgetBaby</p>
                <p class="tl-status">Live on the App Store</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item timeline-active">
              <span class="tl-dot"></span>
              <div>
                <p class="tl-label">PantryBaby</p>
                <p class="tl-status">In development</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item timeline-next">
              <span class="tl-dot"></span>
              <div>
                <p class="tl-label">BabyBlocks Core</p>
                <p class="tl-status">After PantryBaby ships</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="core-visual" aria-hidden="true">
          <div class="core-mock glass">
            <div class="mock-header">
              <span class="mock-icon">🧩</span>
              <span class="mock-name">BabyBlocks Core</span>
            </div>

            <div class="mock-greeting">
              <p class="mock-date">Good morning</p>
              <p class="mock-sub">Here's your day at a glance</p>
            </div>

            <div class="mock-cards">
              <div class="mock-card mock-card--budget">
                <div class="mc-header">
                  <span class="mc-icon">💰</span>
                  <span class="mc-app">BudgetBaby</span>
                </div>
                <p class="mc-value">$47<span class="mc-unit">/day</span></p>
                <p class="mc-label">Safe to Spend</p>
                <div class="mc-bar">
                  <div class="mc-bar-fill" style="width: 62%"></div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="mock-card mock-card--pantry">
                <div class="mc-header">
                  <span class="mc-icon">🥗</span>
                  <span class="mc-app">PantryBaby</span>
                </div>
                <p class="mc-value">8<span class="mc-unit"> items low</span></p>
                <p class="mc-label">Shopping list ready</p>
                <div class="mc-tags">
                  <span class="mc-tag">Milk</span>
                  <span class="mc-tag">Coffee</span>
                  <span class="mc-tag">+6</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="mock-insight">
              <span class="mock-insight-icon">💡</span>
              <p>You usually spend £90 at the supermarket. Your budget allows £104 this week.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What Core does -->
  <section class="what-core section-sm">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header centered">
        <span class="eyebrow">The concept</span>
        <h2>One screen. Every app.</h2>
        <p>BabyBlocks Core doesn't replace your individual apps. It amplifies them. It's the layer that sees the whole picture and tells you what matters today.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="core-features">
        <GlassCard glow>
          <div class="cf-item">
            <div class="cf-icon">📊</div>
            <h3>Unified daily dashboard</h3>
            <p>
              Your BudgetBaby Safe to Spend, PantryBaby shopping list status, and data from every
              future BabyBlocks app, surfaced in one place every morning. No app-switching to get the big picture.
            </p>
          </div>
        </GlassCard>

        <GlassCard glow>
          <div class="cf-item">
            <div class="cf-icon">🔗</div>
            <h3>Cross-app insights</h3>
            <p>
              When BudgetBaby and PantryBaby know about each other, things get smarter.
              Core can flag that your grocery budget is healthy but your pantry suggests a big shop coming,
              so you can plan ahead instead of being surprised.
            </p>
          </div>
        </GlassCard>

        <GlassCard glow>
          <div class="cf-item">
            <div class="cf-icon">📱</div>
            <h3>Home Screen widgets</h3>
            <p>
              See your Safe to Spend and pantry status from the iOS Home Screen without opening a single app.
              Small, medium, and large widget options for whatever fits your lock screen or Home Screen layout.
            </p>
          </div>
        </GlassCard>

        <GlassCard glow>
          <div class="cf-item">
            <div class="cf-icon">🔔</div>
            <h3>Unified notification centre</h3>
            <p>
              All BabyBlocks notifications in one place. Budget period ending, items running low, bills due.
              One notification centre with control over what matters to you, not a flood from three separate apps.
            </p>
          </div>
        </GlassCard>

        <GlassCard glow>
          <div class="cf-item">
            <div class="cf-icon">🔑</div>
            <h3>Single shared account</h3>
            <p>
              One BabyBlocks account. One sign-in. Your data across every app, with household sharing,
              cloud sync, and backup managed from a single settings panel instead of per-app configuration.
            </p>
          </div>
        </GlassCard>

        <GlassCard glow>
          <div class="cf-item">
            <div class="cf-icon">🎯</div>
            <h3>Life goals, not just app goals</h3>
            <p>
              Budget less and eat better. Save £200 before the summer holiday. Reduce food waste this month.
              Core lets you set goals that span multiple apps and tracks progress across all of them together.
            </p>
          </div>
        </GlassCard>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The philosophy -->
  <section class="philosophy section-sm">
    <div class="container-sm">
      <div class="section-header centered">
        <span class="eyebrow">Why now</span>
        <h2>The ecosystem needs a home.</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="phil-grid">
        <GlassCard padding="lg">
          <div class="phil-item">
            <h3>Built last, not first</h3>
            <p>
              We deliberately didn't build Core first. A hub app with nothing to connect is just a marketing page.
              We're building the individual apps first, each one complete and valuable on its own,
              then connecting them when there's actually something worth connecting.
            </p>
            <p>
              BabyBlocks Core ships after PantryBaby because that's when the connection becomes real.
              Two apps. Real cross-app data. Genuine insight.
            </p>
          </div>
        </GlassCard>

        <GlassCard padding="lg">
          <div class="phil-item">
            <h3>Clarity at scale</h3>
            <p>
              Every individual app is designed to answer one question clearly. BabyBlocks Core is
              designed to answer a bigger question: <em>"How am I actually doing today?"</em>
            </p>
            <p>
              As the ecosystem grows, Core grows with it. Each new app adds a new dimension to the daily
              picture without ever turning it into a dashboard you have to decode.
            </p>
          </div>
        </GlassCard>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Stay in the loop -->
  <section class="notify-section section-sm">
    <div class="container-sm">
      <GlassCard accent padding="lg">
        <div class="notify-inner">
          <div>
            <p class="notify-label">Stay in the loop</p>
            <h2>First, let's ship PantryBaby.</h2>
            <p>
              BabyBlocks Core comes after PantryBaby. The best thing you can do right now is
              follow along as PantryBaby develops, and let us know what you want Core to do.
            </p>
            <div class="notify-actions">
              <a href="/coming-soon/pantrybaby" class="btn btn-primary">
                Follow PantryBaby →
              </a>
              <a href="https://babyblocks.canny.io/feature-requests" class="btn btn-secondary" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
                Request a Core feature →
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="notify-icon" aria-hidden="true">🧩</div>
        </div>
      </GlassCard>
    </div>
  </section>
</LayoutCore>

<style>
  /* Hero */
  .core-hero {
    padding-top: calc(var(--space-20) + var(--space-8));
  }

  .core-inner {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 380px;
    gap: var(--space-16);
    align-items: center;
  }

  .core-copy {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-6);
  }

  .core-copy h1 {
    font-size: clamp(var(--text-5xl), 8vw, var(--text-7xl));
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    line-height: 0.95;
  }

  .core-tagline {
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    font-weight: var(--weight-semibold);
    color: var(--text-primary) !important;
    margin: 0 !important;
  }

  .core-desc {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    max-width: 52ch;
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
  }

  /* Timeline */
  .core-timeline {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    padding-top: var(--space-2);
  }

  .timeline-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }

  .tl-dot {
    width: 12px;
    height: 12px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .timeline-done .tl-dot   { background: var(--green); }
  .timeline-active .tl-dot { background: #C8922A; box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(200, 146, 42, 0.2); }
  .timeline-next .tl-dot   { background: var(--accent); box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px var(--accent-dim); }

  .tl-label {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: var(--weight-semibold);
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .tl-status {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .timeline-done  .tl-label { color: var(--text-secondary); }
  .timeline-active .tl-label { color: #C8922A; }
  .timeline-next  .tl-label { color: var(--accent); }

  /* Mock UI */
  .core-mock {
    padding: var(--space-6);
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.78) !important;
    border-color: var(--glass-border-accent) !important;
    box-shadow: 0 0 40px rgba(107, 95, 199, 0.1), var(--shadow-xl);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }

  .mock-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-2);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: var(--weight-bold);
    color: var(--text-primary);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .mock-icon { font-size: 1.3rem; }

  .mock-greeting { padding: var(--space-1) 0; }

  .mock-date {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    font-weight: var(--weight-bold);
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin: 0;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .mock-sub {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .mock-cards {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }

  .mock-card {
    padding: var(--space-4);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    border: 1px solid var(--glass-border);
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.02);
  }

  .mc-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-2);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .mc-icon { font-size: 1rem; }

  .mc-app {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: var(--weight-semibold);
    color: var(--text-muted);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  }

  .mc-value {
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    line-height: 1;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-1);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .mc-unit {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: var(--weight-medium);
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .mc-label {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-3);
  }

  .mc-bar {
    height: 4px;
    background: var(--glass-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-full);
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .mc-bar-fill {
    height: 100%;
    background: var(--accent);
    border-radius: var(--radius-full);
  }

  .mock-card--pantry .mc-bar-fill { background: #4A7B6E; }

  .mc-tags {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-2);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .mc-tag {
    font-size: var(--text-2xs);
    padding: 2px var(--space-2);
    background: rgba(74, 123, 110, 0.1);
    border: 1px solid rgba(74, 123, 110, 0.18);
    border-radius: var(--radius-full);
    color: #4A7B6E;
    font-weight: var(--weight-semibold);
  }

  .mock-insight {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-4);
    background: rgba(107, 95, 199, 0.07);
    border: 1px solid rgba(107, 95, 199, 0.15);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  }

  .mock-insight-icon { font-size: 1rem; flex-shrink: 0; line-height: 1.4; }

  .mock-insight p {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Features */
  .core-features {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }

  .cf-item {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }

  .cf-icon { font-size: 2rem; line-height: 1; }
  .cf-item h3 { font-size: var(--text-lg); }

  .cf-item p {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
  }

  /* Philosophy */
  .phil-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-5);
  }

  .phil-item {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }

  .phil-item h3 { font-size: var(--text-xl); }

  .phil-item p {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
  }

  /* Notify */
  .notify-inner {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: var(--space-8);
  }

  .notify-label {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: var(--weight-semibold);
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2) !important;
  }

  .notify-inner h2 { font-size: var(--text-2xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-3); }

  .notify-inner > div > p {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    max-width: 46ch;
  }

  .notify-actions {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .notify-icon { font-size: 4rem; line-height: 1; flex-shrink: 0; opacity: 0.45; }

  @media (max-width: 1000px) {
    .core-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .core-visual { order: -1; max-width: 400px; }
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .core-features { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
    .phil-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .notify-inner { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; }
    .notify-icon { display: none; }
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .core-features { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .notify-actions { flex-direction: column; }
  }
</style>
